HEADWORD: Scientifically
<hw>Sci`en*tif"ic*al*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a scientific
manner; according to the rules or principles of science.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is easier to believe than to be <qex>scientifically</qex>
instructed.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

